The paper deals with speech recognition in the presence of interfering background speech, which is a problem in the field of speech processing and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.SD (Sound) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes end-to-end models, which are often used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Learning) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper uses attention mechanisms and multi-task learning, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
